headline: ResMed’s Q3 Earnings Call: Our Top 5 Analyst Questions
summary: ResMed’s third quarter results aligned with Wall Street’s revenue expectations, while its non-GAAP earnings per share moderately outpaced consensus. Management attributed the quarter’s performance to robust demand for both devices and masks, particularly in the U.S., Canada, and Latin America, where mask resupply programs and new product launches drove growth.
